				\begin{document}$$\theta _y = \left| {P_y} \right|{\mathrm{/}}P\sim 0.1$$\end{document}, where P is the electron momentum and Py denotes its y-component). These electrons form dense jets, with the density njet ~ 5nc initially, however, it decreases rapidly due to dispersion in the z-direction. The total charge of the jets is ~0.2 nC.

