It is generally understood that the jets are accelerated out of the reconnection region by the magnetic tension forces (Tm = (B·∇)B/4π) of the newly connected, strongly bent magnetic field lines. In Fig. 3, we plot the magnetic fields at x = 26λ0, and the z-component of the magnetic tension force Tzm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
