				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\bar E_{\mathrm{k}}$$\end{document} ~ 38 keV. Using the reconnection magnetic field ~100 MG and electron density ~1nc, the plasma β is ~0.15. As the electrons are gaining energy during the reconnection process, the value of β increases with time, but it does not change significantly (β ≈ 0.07–0.22 for t = 32–36T0), and during the whole reconnection process the adjacent plasma is maintained in the magnetically dominated regime.

